The Office of the Vice President has announced staff changes, with Melanie Kaye, the Director of Communications to Dr. Jill Biden, departing the White House. She is succeeded by James M. Gleeson, who previously worked in the U.S. House of Representatives as the Communications Director to Congressman Xavier Becerra. Gleeson has experience in coordinating communications strategy and messaging efforts for House Democrats since 2009. Before that, he worked as an Account Manager for a political consulting firm and served in the Colorado State House. Gleeson attended Arapahoe Community College and the University of Colorado, Boulder. He currently resides in Silver Spring, Maryland with his wife.